sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Administrator
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Operator Controller<br/>Watch API
    participant Components as Component Namespaces<br/>Various Resources
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus (ODH)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant OSMonitoring as OpenShift Monitoring<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Note over Admin,Components: Flow 1: DataScienceCluster Creation and Component Deployment

    Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply DataScienceCluster<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>OAuth/Cert Auth
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate DSC<br/>HTTPS/9443 TLS1.2+<br/>TLS Client Cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch Event (DSC Created)<br/>Watch API TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read DSC Spec<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Component Resources<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>Components: Apply Manifests<br/>API Calls TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update DSC Status<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over Prometheus,OSMonitoring: Flow 2: Monitoring and Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Controller: Scrape Metrics<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>No Auth (NetworkPolicy)
    Prometheus->>Components: Scrape Component Metrics<br/>HTTP/HTTPS Various<br/>Bearer Token
    OSMonitoring->>Prometheus: Scrape ODH Prometheus<br/>HTTPS/9091 TLS1.2+<br/>Bearer Token

    Note over Controller,Components: Flow 3: Component Manifest Application

    Controller->>Controller: Read Embedded Manifests<br/>Filesystem I/O<br/>No Encryption
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Apply Kustomize Output<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Components: Create Resources<br/>Watch API TLS1.2+<br/>Component SA Tokens

    Note over Controller,Components: Flow 4: Service Mesh Integration (KServe)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Istio Gateway<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create VirtualService<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Deploy KServe Controller<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Components->>K8sAPI: KServe → Knative Serving<br/>API Calls TLS1.2+<br/>KServe SA Token
